                            <comment id="14081975" author="anoop.hbase" created="Fri, 1 Aug 2014 06:27:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In tests where we have  some more test code after catch,  we wont be able to do this&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;try&lt;/p&gt;
{
...
fail()
}
&lt;p&gt;catch(Exception e) {&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;br/&gt;
....&lt;br/&gt;
....&lt;br/&gt;
....&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14082021" author="busbey" created="Fri, 1 Aug 2014 07:26:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It depends on the code. While there are some that can&apos;t be updated, in some cases we just have clean up code which can still be done in a finally block, or an After annotation. In some other cases we&apos;re combining a failure test and a non-failure test and we could refactor those into individual tests.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14133366" author="dimaspivak" created="Sun, 14 Sep 2014 20:02:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d like to work on this next week, if that&apos;s alright. I&apos;m really excited about getting more familiar with our unit tests in general and committing myself to this seems like good motivation. &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14133513" author="busbey" created="Mon, 15 Sep 2014 02:47:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That sounds great. When you have a patch, please put it up on reviewboard and address it to the hbase group. Feel free to add me as a reviewer as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
